The paper deals with improving the spectral efficiency in the MIMO broadcast channel with delayed and quantized channel state information. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed strategy involves adjusting the number of active users to balance various gains and inter-user interference, which involves system-level optimization (cs.SY). The paper also deals with multi-user MIMO (cs.MM) and proposes a strategy that can be easily combined with round-robin scheduling, which involves algorithmic development (cs.LG).
